HEADWORD: Kussier
<hw>Kus"si*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
Turkish instrument of music, with a hollow body covered with skin, over
which five strings are stretched.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kussir</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

